inn1.comm: starts off with a length ball angling across - the other night Harris got appreciable outswing
goes through with the angle again, Butt - as with the first delivery - leaves it alone
ad again, angling across him, pretty wide, and But shoulders arms again
one more delivery allowed to go through undisturbed to the keeper

oh what a soft dismissal, four deliveries wide of him and left alone, Harris bowls in the same area again, and Butt chases it. No feet involved, just a tentative push away from the body, and the edge settles comfortably in Haddin's gloves
and Harris begins with a wicket-maiden again, just like two nights ago. He might want to dig this pitch up and take home. This one Younis leaves alone outside off
starts with a shot delivery, tucking Latif up, who goes back and across and defends
fuller, presents it the full face, not much intent to find gaps
stays in the crease and defends a length delivery
slightly back of a length, across him, played with an open face towards point

and just like that, another one goes, stays back to a fullish delivery, plays in front of his body, and it goes in the air to the left of Johnson, whose left hand pushes Pakistan down to 2 for 0! It wasn't even a slower one - 146ks. If somebody's slower ball comes at 146ks, though, devil save us from the faster one. There was a puff of dust when the ball pitched, so it could just have stopped at Latif
oh my word, that's the quicker one! back of a length, rising outside off, at 153.6ks, folks you have got to believe my eyes, Malik fends and is beaten
right on the money Harris, Younis goes deep in the crease and defends
opens the face on it, can't get it past point
shorter outside off, left alone
nearly an lbw, stuck on the crease, the ball comes back in, the height - he is hit in the thigh - saves him
finally Pakistan are away, Younis plays in front of his body, gets the inside half of his bat, and gets a couple through midwicket
sharper delivery, more effort, shorter, outside off, and left alone
full delivery, nicely punched down the ground, Johnson sticks his left hand out and fields
oh, stays low at 150ks, just outside off, and hits a crack and goes second bounce to Haddin
slower ball outside off, defended

more drama here, Ponting at point claims a catch, Malik reckons it's a bump ball. Third umpire's verdict awaited. Malik is safe, it is a fulltoss that he has driven straight into the ground, it was close so no harm in checking
shorter delivery, angling across Malik, and he lets this one be
Malik's off the mark too, opens the face late on it, and gets a single down to third man
length delivery, just outside off, comes forward and defends
slightly shorter, keeps Malik on the crease, defended without trouble
short and wide, Malik sees a release shot, but goes too hard at it and is beaten
runs this one down to third man for a single
shout for lbw, but it's angling down the leg side, Younis falls over while looking to work it to leg and misses. Bowled from behind the crease, it seemed like - no replays so not sure
shorter, just outside off, and he shoulders arms
stays back and defends a length delivery angled across him
gets the edge with a back of a length delivery, but it's too thick and the ball travels towards third man
slower ball, Younis stays back and defends
short, rising high towards the chest, Younis jumps, rides the bounce, and keeps the defensive shot down
this time he doesn't fend, he stays inside the line and lets it go through to Haddin
fuller this time, but not driveable, Younis goes back and across and defends
length delivery just outside off, Malik covers the stumps and shoulders arms
slightly shorter, closer to off stump, Malik has to play at it, he pushes it towards cover
overpitched, no swing, and angled into the pads, nicely clipped away through midwicket
short, angling in, Younis sways out, leaves the bat hanging - quite reminiscent of his dismissal in the third ODI, but the ball doesn't come in enough this time
driven, again early into the shot, the bat face turns towards leg, hence it goes in the air but bounces short of mid-off
comes forward and pushes this one to cover
looking for swing, there is none to be found, and overpitches on the leg stump, Malik clips it through midwicket, a shot that comes naturally to him
short again, into the ribs, this time worked away safely towards square leg

a word of caution for Malik too, he need to be quick and decisive with a Johnson bouncer, else he will keep pinging him in the helmet like he did just now. Bowled at 150ks, the bouncer rises towards the head, Malik is like a rabbit in the headlights, just turns his head away late, the ball hits the shoulder and then the helmet. No pain showed, though
Ponting follows that bouncer up with a diving save at backward point, good stuff by Australia all around

lovely straight-drive, overpitched just outside off, and he just meets it with a straight bat, no big back lift, no big followthrough, just good connection with full face. The push-drive brings Pakistan's first boundary
Younis drives again, and the bat turns in his hand early again, and instead of mid-off, the shot goes towards mid-on
gets a stride in this time, and defends towards cover - all those loose drives have been the ones that he has played in front of his body
half-volley outside off, hit powerfully, but straight to mid-off
angling in to Younis this time, he presses forward and defends it to leg

another Aussie bowler gets a wicket in his first over - actually all three have struck with their fifth deliveries! And another soft dismissal here, this is a length delivery fairly wide of off, Younis gets half a move forward and pushes at it away from his body, the edge is snapped by Haddin
three bowlers tried so far, and all three have started with wicket-maidens! Akmal stays on the crease and defends this length delivery
short, sharp, just outside off, gets on top of it and defends
makes him jump around in the crease, and he has no clue when the ball bounced and took the leading edge and went over gully
another edge, and this one falls way short of White at second slip. Good sharp delivery, just outside off, has to play at it
beats him outside off, short of a length, close to off, makes him play, and then the angle beats him
fuller, wider, and left alone this time
sure signs of dual bounce, hits a crack at back of a length, and bounces another time before reaching Haddin
accurate, just around off, defended off the back foot
just back of a length, around middle and leg, pushed towards midwicket
leaves this one alone outside off
fuller, closer to off, presses half-forward and defends
punched away from outside off, can't get it past cover-point
just back of a length, just outside off, defended, and back-to-back maidens for McKay
starts on target, just off and around, Umar defends off the back foot
length delivery, comes forward and defends this one back to the bowler
back of a length, outside off, gets the outside half of the bat, but is safe
shorter, just outside off, can't do much with that
not this time, he gets a big stride forward and defends towards cover
fuller, beats him outside off, Haddin doesn't collect it cleanly - Hopes may not have got a wicket, but all four bowlers have begun with maidens so far
back of a length, just outside off, and defended towards cover
beaten outside off, almost trying to edge it, looks to run it past the keeper but there are two slips in place, good thing he couldn't play the intended shot
looks to cut, but it is too full for the shot, gets a bottom edge but is safe
stays back and plays with a straight bat this time, back to the bowler
and again, back of a length, no room, and all he can do is defend

slashes outside off, misses it by light years, plays way outside its line - anyway, three maidens in a row for McKay, and three maidens in a row for Australia. One run has been scored in last five overs!
can't get it off the square, stays back and defends an accurate delivery that is just short of a good length
clears the front leg and farms this one from outside off to wide of fine leg - first runs in 24 deliveries
legcutter, goes past the tentative poke outside off
stuck in the crease and pushing at a fullish delivery outside off, and is beaten again
and another legcutter outside off, and once again he is stuck on the crease and pokes at it, and once again he misses the edge

how did he miss that one? this is as close to off stump as you can get without actually hitting it, and Umar ends up playing inside the line of it, Haddin is blinded by the bat, and concedes four byes - don't forget Haddin is standing up to the stumps
clipped away off the pads, but a diving Shaun Marsh means McKay is yet to be scored off
wide of off, Malik comes forward and defends
opens up this time, and not much risk in this shot, it's a length ball, wide of off, comes forward, opens the face and goes over cover
gets back to off line, and Malik defends towards cover
shimmies down the pitch, plays with soft hands, and gets a single to wide of backward point
angled into the pads, and worked away for an easy single to fine leg
good running, plays this one with soft hands towards mid-on, and comes through for one
moves across the stumps, and works this one towards square leg for a single
and good running again, soft hands, and the ball has hardly even crossed the stumps at the non-striker's end by the time Akmal makes the single
yes and no with this single to backward point, Umar is quick so Ponting has to go to the non-striker's end, but Malik has made it easily
hit back to the left of Hopes, but he fields well
steered away to third man for the fifth single in the over
moves across, misses out on his attempt to work this fine, can't be given lbw as it is headed down the leg side
this time he gets across again, covers the line of the ball, and then opens his face on it for a single to third man
back of a length, no room, Malik goes back and across and defends
close to off stump, but manges to run it down to third man
leaves this one be outside off
nice shot, good balance, moves across, gets a length delivery and flicks it past square leg - third boundary of the innings
and starts off with a fulltoss, which is worked away past midwicket for one
some drift there as Akmal presses forward and defends this to cover
left alone outside off, not much turn there, and that fools Haddin into conceding a bye
overpitched outside off, played with the turn towards midwicket for a single
looks to cut one that it too full - must say he manages to pull of those shots against offspin - but is beaten this time
plays with a vertical bat now, gets a thick edge towards short third man and completes a sharp single
moves across, pushes this one towards point, NO is the call
slogs, gets a healthy inside edge, and gets two to fine of fine leg
moves across again, but plays this one back to Hopes, on the bounce of course
nice! nearly a slog sweep, moves across again, and gets under this length ball and goes up and over midwicket
immediate pulling back of length, defended towards point
rides the bounce this time and steers it to third man for one
cuts, cuts straight to Hopes at backward point
driven against the spin, but his foot is close to the pitch, and gets a couple to wide of sweeper-cover
beaten on the cut again, too full again
manages to cut this one, gets a single to deep point
helped away to just wide of short third and gets an easy single
cuts again, this time the length is there, but the sharp turn beats him
educated edge, flicks the webbing on Haddin's glove on the way to the boundary. Can't really call it a drop, nor a deliberate shot. Haddin is standing up to the stumps, remember
defends this one off the front foot
looks for the heave over midwicket, doesn't quite connect, but manages to keep it down
this is played deliberately, and hence much squarer than that boundary, will get a single to third man
comes forward, defends towards cover
beaten outside off, goes for the single to third man, but plays under the delivery
looks for the single to third man, but the turn cramps him up
fuller, Malik lets this one through to the keeper
shorter, this one gives him time to dab it down to third man
the Akmal-Hauritz cut-and-mouse continues, gets a bottom edge on this one as it is too full
this time he is beaten by the arm ball wide outside off, doesn't turn, passes over the white marker, and is called wide
paddled away from outside off, gets a single
driven against the turn, but close to the body, and gets a single to sweeper-cover
pushed towards deep point, by the time the sweeper-cover comes around, he comes back for two - turned blind too
onto the pads, worked around the corner for one
good running again, soft hands, towards mid-off, and he is out of the blocks right away
slower offcutter, 131ks, beats Malik as he looks to defend outside off
full delivery, punched down the ground, nice shot but Johnson gets his leg around and ricochets it towards cover
beaten outside off again, this seems to be deliberately thrown wide outside off, and Malik is nowhere near it as he cuts
paddled away from outside off again, gets a single to fine leg
swept from way outside off, gets a single to fine leg
good running again, paddles it from outside off, hasn't hit it hard and comes back for two, would have made it even if Harris had hit direct
beaten again, goes for the big drive against the spin, some drift there takes it away from him and beats him
another paddle sweep, from way outside off
steps out, Hauritz bowls it short, Malik checks the shot and hits it uppishly towards Hauritz
moves across the stumps, looks to drop and run, but Hussey is alert at cover and charges in to keep them in the crease
good hustling again, on the pads, worked away with soft hands, and straight away they know they want two, and the pressure results in a fumble from Marsh who is running in from deep square
goes for the full and wide delivery, and it's too wide

what a ripper from Johnson, first the short lifter tucks Umar Akmal up, and almost by habit Umar sets off for a run even though he has been pushed deep inside the crease, Malik doesn't hesitate either. This time the ball hasn't gone too far, and Johnson comes around, fields, and finds Malik short with an underarm flick
goers for the yorker, but is too wide, and squeezed through covers
goes back and across and defends it outside off
fuller, on the pads, flicked away towards fine leg
the paddle sweep again, gets a single
angling in, turns away, played with soft hands towards point, gets a single
tip-and-run again, towards cover this time
full delivery, pushed to the left of point for a single
cuts a fullish delivery, can't find the point-short-third gap
the paddle sweep again, and he gets another single to fine leg
goes for the big slog right away, misses by a long way, Haddin removes the bails, but the back foot is grounded
goes for the scoop shot, misses, is saved the lbw because of the angle
more conventional shot, drive down the ground, gets a single to wide of mid-off
thick outside edge as he looks to defend, so thick it goes towards point
fuller delivery, pushed down to mid-off
short and wide, steered away to third man for a single
tossed up around middle, straightens upon pitching, defended
opens the face this time, but can't force it past short cover
again no room for him, dead-bats it
arm ball, fried into the pads, misses
sweeps, sweeps fine, finds short fine leg
tossed up again, around middle, plays with a straight bat this time and gets a single to long-off
extravagant flick over square leg, just half a step out of the crease, and the length ball goes sailing over square leg
lets this one go through to Haddin outside off
Umar Akmal is almost run out, looks for a cheeky single to point, is sent back rightly, Ponting shies, and it ricochets off Umar's bat for four overhtrows
steers down to third man, gets a single
moves across looking for a slog over midwicket, aborts the shot and defends because the length is short
on the pads and helped away to deep square leg for a single
leaps out of his crease, Hauritz bowls wide and shirt, but he gets his bat down
back to the paddle sweep, and he gets a single to fine leg
open face from Alam again, can't get it past point, though
this is too full, and this one he manages to place past cover
cuts, connects, can't get past backward point
short, turning in, cramps him up as he looks to late-cut
Alam wafts at it and misses, playing inside the line
thick edge as he pushes at it outside off, gets a single to third man
Akmal stays deep in the crease and defends a back-of-a-length delivery
fuller, he comes forward and defends, no room to work with
full, overpitched, stays back still, and hits it one-bounce to Hopes
short and wider, and he steers it late, getting it fine of Harris at third man, fine enough to come back for two
short and wide , cut away towards deep point
full outside off, is beaten on the cut shot
slows this one down, 82ks, surprises Akmal who pushes at it early and is beaten
paddle sweep back again, gets him a single
angled into the pads, worked around the corner for one
cuts straight to backward point, doesn't want the single, but Ponting hits the stumps direct and gives away an overthrow
wants a sharp single but hasn't hit it wide enough of Hussey at cover
moves across, swipes, gets a single to deep midwicket
goes past the outside edge as Alam plays a nothing shot to the delivery angling across
short, cut away, one bounce to Ponting at point
another short delivery, pulls this one, awkwardly, gets a single to mid-on
this time he drops and runs to the left of Hussey at cover, not his natural throwing side
swept away, regulation sweep, square of Harris at fine leg, gets a couple
driven against the spin, a diving Hussey at cover saves one
back to paddle sweep, and another single to fine leg
short, pushed towards sweeper-cover for one
too wide for the paddle sweep, goes over the white line and is called wide
opens the face and pinches a single to the right of backward point
around the off line, and defended towards cover
Harris resumes angling down the pads, and is worked away for a single
slashed, slashed hard, gets a thick edge that goes wide of the long arm of White at first slip
this is cut off the middle of the bat, powerfully, but gets  just one because Marsh does well at deep point
stays on the crease, looks to drop and run on the off, but has hit it too hard
length ball, driven through covers, gets a single to sweeper-cover
aggressive shot, goes over the covers, doesn't connect well, which is good for him as this one bounces short of sweeper-cover
topspinner, cramps him up for room
overpitched on the pads, swept away for one to fine leg
short, slow, cut away in front of square, and that's yet another 50 for Umar - can he go onto a hundred?
sweeps, gets the glove to this and it goes fine of fine leg for a couple
plays down the ground with soft hands, and comes through for a single, would have been tight if Johnson had hit direct from mid-on
cuts, gets a single, Hauritz ends with 0 for 38 in 10
starts off with a slower ball, 118ks - slower as opposed to what, I know not - and is pushed down the ground for a single to long-off
length ball, just outside off, angling in, played towards cover
pushes forward, McKay digs it in short, and Alam flat-bats past mid-off, but Harris does real well with the chase, slides and stops, gets back up and throws to the far end
another short ball, this time he pulls, and misses
slower ball again, pushes this one to sweeper-cover
moves across, looking to open the leg side, but McKay is sharp and accurate, and Akmal defends
on the pads, and worked away for an easy single
pulled away fine, McKay makes a good diving save at the fine-leg boundary
tucked away off the hips for a single to square leg
driven inside-out, wide of sweeper-cover, gets a couple
short and wide, cut away, gets another single
hit powerfully back, McKay fields it to his right
fuller, into the pads, pushed down to long-on for one
nice punch down the ground, on the up, gets a single
short, and cut away, gets a single to sweeper-cover
slower ball, he has got one of the best changes of pace in the pace, and Akmal plays way before the ball arrives
moves across, swipes across this good-length delivery, gets a single to long-on
looks for the big hit, doesn't get it right, gets just a single down to long-off
goes for the yorker, but turns out to be a half-volley on the pads, worked away for one to deep square
slower ball, angling down the pads, gets a leg-bye to short fine
drives this one away from his body, gets a single to deep point
slower legcutter, they take a sharp single, by the time Hussey at backward point gets around and throws and Haddin removes the bail, Alam's dive has carried him in. A direct hit would have got him
looks to crash this through covers, can't find the gap
he has slog-swept a fast bowler for six! moves across early, gets into position, and connects sweetly as he goes over midwicket
looks to push and run, Alam sees it is hit too powerfully to Hussey at cover, and sends Akmal back
slower ball, inside-out, good shot, past cover, wide of sweeper-cover, gets a couple
slower ball again, but the drop in pace is not as big, 132ks, and it's full and straight, and Akmal is too early into the slog shot over midwicket, and ends up playing all around it
is greeted with a bouncer, pretty accurate too, and ducks into it
moves across, looking to go fine on the on side, misses the short delivery
short, angling into the body, keeps the pull shot down, gets a single to fine leg

length ball, doesn't go for the big shot but for the single, Ponting dives full length to his left from midwicket, back-hand-flicks it as he is diving, doesn't find the stumps, would have been tight had he hit direct
pushes down the ground, and hands over the strike to Boom Boom
bouncer is the clear plan, but this one is too short and too high
Boom Boom goes Bust - another bouncer, Afridi pulls off the front foot, gets it high on the bat, and it lobs towards mid-off, where Hauritz takes a smart catch running forward
punched away crisply, wide of deep point, gets a couple
fuller, brings him onto the front foot, and he hits straight to cover
teases him with a wide delivery, Alam is not close to it as he cuts, and misses
upper-cut, nicely played, Marsh runs around from deep point, fields it just inside the rope and relays it to Hopes, third man, even as he falls over the rope
is beaten on the regulation cut shot this time
goes for the yorker, gets it right, but the inside edge takes it past the keeper for four
that's fifty for Alam, drives this full delivery down to long-on, second ODI fifty for Alam
slower ball, runs it down to third man, wide of Harris, and comes back for two
slower ball outside off, can't get it past point as he opens the face on it
pushes this off the front foot, gets a single to wide of cover
gets big on Sarfraz, back of a length, holds its line, and beats a poke
looks to sweep - I kid you not - proper sweep, not even slog-sweep, and misses completely outside off
stays back and looks to cut, and plays all over it
goes back into the crease, wants a single to point, Alam sends him back
slower ball, dropped it at his feet and run, it looks like it is going back to McKay and would result in a run-out, but it turns away
he is looking to sweep another fast bowler - at the WACA!, is hit in the helmet, is disoriented for a bit as Haddin nearly runs him out
looks to run this down to third man, and nearly plays it on
slower ball, this team he can lean back and get a single to third man
incredible slower ball, this is the slow slower delivery, 109ks, has no idea about this legcutter as he shuts his eyes and prays this one doesn't hit the stumps - it doesn't
medium slower ball, plays in front of his body, gets a single to long-off
hits a length ball down to long-off
short delivery, bounces well, runs it down to third man for one
slower ball, on the pads, flicked away for a single to short fine
backs away, Johnson goes full and wide, and Sarfraz doesn't have a play on it
makes room and toe-ends straight to extra cover, White wouldn't miss this one
length ball on the pads, and worked away for a single
Rana jumps out, gets enough on the mis-hit to clear the cover ring
yorker, 143ks, can't do anything with it
pushes a length delivery towards square leg for a single
Alam is still nudging and running, gets a single to point
superb shot, backs away, Harris goes for the yorker, misses the length by inches, and he smokes this low fulltoss through the gap between mid-off and extra cover

that's No. 3 for Harris, the third five-for is still on! Rana is expecting a yorker and stays in the crease, Harris doesn't go for the yorker, instead a fast and straight length delivery, aimed for the off stump, Rana pushes at it away from his body, and loses his off stump
length ball, into the pads, and Alam takes a single, he is not farming the strike
immaculately placed, jumping in his crease, gets a soft edge, that bounces short and goes smack through the keeper-slip gap
on the pads, turned away for a single
slower ball, played in front of his body, manages to get it wide enough of Johnson
another one takes it in the helmet - Rao, after Malik and Sarfraz - this is a sharp bouncer, Rao gets in line to fend, but realises it has got big, and takes his eye off and presents it the helmet
backs a way a touch, Johnson bowls full and wide, Rao misses
takes off from foot marks, it's full and straight, and Haddin does well to recover and collect it head high
good shot, straight over mid-off, backs away, gets under a length delivery, and hits it smack over mid-off, 200 up - didn't look likely after the first 13 overs
short and sharp, hurries him up into the pull shot, beats him
length ball, crashed down the ground, gets a single
that is an amazing shot! Walks across the stumps, gets inside the line, and whips this short ball flat over fine leg. Harris is looking for five, he gets six!
square drive, mis-hits, but gets it over point
Rao Iftikhar is playing a ripper, slower ball, and he backs away and waits and crashes it through covers, bang off the middle of the bat

Ponting picks this one late, and then virtually flies across to hold onto this one. McKay goes fast and follows a backing-away Rao, and gets out a limp shot, lobbed towards midwicket where Ponting does the rest
Yes he can! Alam gets too much under this length delivery and can't clear mid-on

inn2.comm: gets shape away from the left-hand batsman, Marsh gets on top of it and drives to cover

and Pakistan start off with missing a dolly of a run-out! Yes-no-yes-no has both Marsh and Haddin shaking hands and returning, Khalid Latif fields from square leg, running in, can almost run to the stumps and get him, he goes for the underarm flick and misses by a fair bit. And no wicketkeeper in sight either
shoulders arms to a delivery wide of off
gets forward and defends a length delivery
back of a length, angled across, defended off the back foot
sharp delivery, pitches middle and moves in, raps him on the thigh
this one leaves him, and Marsh has to play at him and is beaten - all through Pakistan's horror tour, Asif's bowling has been a soothing presence, just like this over
Haddin drives the first delivery on the up, wide too it is, but he hits it right in the middle of the bat, finds cover fielder, though
angling down the leg side, and helped away towards fine leg
shapes back in, Marsh defends off the front foot
goes with the angle, comes forward and pushes towards cover
on target, just outside off, holding its line a touch, no room
good short-arm pull, off the hip, over square leg, flat hit
short and wide, cut away towards third man
thick edge, pushing away from his body, gets a single to third man
Haddin is lucky here, goes for an on-the-up over-mid-off shot, the ball is not nearly full enough, but he just gets enough to beat Afridi running back from mid-off
inside edge, slightly tentative in pushing at this outside off
sharp single, drops it off the wicket, and rushes through
another beauty from Asif, back of a length, pitches leg, seams away, and misses the edge by inches
slightly short of a length, punched back to the bowler
shapes away from Haddin, stays low too, and beats his attempt at a drive through covers
well bowled, just short of a length, shaping away, and no room to do anything with it
good-looking drive, on the up, high elbow, Malik fields at short cover
works it off the pads, wide of mid-on, gets a single
nicely played, just a push-drive, between backward point and cover-point, gets a couple
runs this off the face of his bat for one to third man
works this off his hips, soft hands, square of fine leg, gets a couple
angled across off, comes forward, thinks of a drive, but lets it go through to the keeper
around off, pitched up, Marsh comes forward and defends
short delivery, tucks him up, looking to shape up for the pull, but it's too quick for him
short and wide, and gloriously cut away, goes deep in the crease and waits and places it wide of point
Haddin is gone! goes for one forceful shot too many, looking to go over covers but the ball isn't full enough for that, and Shoaib Malik takes a comfortable catch at cover
and gets a thick edge straight away, plays back to a fullish delivery that shapes away, and takes the edge and flies past the first slip, the only slip
fuller around off, still stays back to defend
stays back still, pushes a length ball to mid-on
stays low, just outside off, Ponting gets his bat down, and ends up in the squatting position
call him stubborn but this is an incredible shot, stays back to a length delivery and punches it past point, superb timing
worked fine off the hips, fine of fine leg, comes back for a risky second, Rana's throw is in quick but about a couple of feet too high, and that gets Marsh in. Third umpire says not out
dropped, sharp half chance at short cover, Marsh has hit a scorcher on the up, to Malik's right, he gets a touch on it, but can't hold on. Would have been a special catch had he held on
ooof what a shot, slightly into the pads, and he has flicked it no fuss at all, right off the middle of the bat, no effort, just timing, past square leg
shorter, Ponting goes deep in the crease, gets an inside edge onto the pad
gets back and across and defends a shortish delivery
goes back and across again, and punches one towards short cover
short, pulled, top edge, but the fine leg is up in the circle - good bouncer, over off and just outside, gets an edge, but goes for four. Cruel game
fuller delivery, Marsh stays in the crease and defends
on the pads, and worked away for a single to deep square leg
beauty, angling in, starting to move away before pitching, and then taking off upon pitching, six inches closer to the stumps, and it would have taken the edge
gets closer to the stumps, Ponting goes back and pushes it to mid-off
short of a length, outside off, takes it from there and pushes it to mid-on
angled across the left-hand batsman, Marsh shoulders arms
full, on off stump, pushed down to Afridi at mid-off
back of a length, tucks him up around the hip
angled across the stumps, runs this one down to third man
lovely shot, just back of a length, moves across, and short-arms this past the short fine leg - not looking to hit it hard, keeping it down
goes back and across, right behind the line, and punches it down to mid-off
shapes up for the drive, delays the shot to push it past point, placement over timing. Alam fumbles in the deep, gets him three
fullish delivery, Ponting stays on the crease and defends
misses out on a leg-side offering, sort of falling over while flicking, and hits it straight towards midwicket
full outside off, shaping away, Ponting lunges forward and shoulders arms
back of a length again, Ponting goes back and across and plays it to mid-on
punched off the back foot, right on his toes as it gets big on him, uppishly through cover, "catch it" is the shout, but it's wide of short cover
looks to steer it to third man, but can't get it past point
looks to cut, a touch too full for it, is beaten
cut away powerfully, one bounce to cover-point
lovely straight drive, but too straight, hits the stumps at non-striker's end
another powerful square cut, but straight to cover-point again
pulls, the ball stays low, and passes underneath the bat outside off, maiden over
punched off the back foot, gets his first non-boundary runs, a single to sweeper-cover
defended off the back foot, towards cover
another cut shot goes to hand, backward point this time

again a cut shot goes to hand, but this time not on the bounce, has to be at least a fifth cut for no runs from Marsh, a touch too full perhaps for the shot and he hits neck high to Alam at backward point - not all the way back at the edge of the circle, a sort of short backward point
pushes forward outside off and shoulders arms
leaves another ball outside off be
Ponting moves back and across, and pushes it to midwicket
moves across again, stays back, and helps it to wide of midwicket for a single
White stays with shouldering arms to semi-wide deliveries outside off
back of a length, rising delivery, defended back to the bowler
forward defensive to a length ball outside off
guided straight to backward point, and yells out a NO right away
angling into the pads, goes back, can't place it past midwicket
short and wide, and punched away to deep point for a single
good hit down the ground, nicely timed, but Rana at mid-on makes a diving save
short and wide, a touch of extra bounce, White gets on top of it, but can't get the cut past point
fuller delivery, closer to the stumps, White comes forward and leaves it be
steps down the track, looks for a flicked single, can't get it off the square - 10 balls for no runs for White
that's the trademark Ponting pull, swivels as he does so, nice sweet sound of the bat, gets a single to square leg
oh that's the other variety, White doesn't care he is on the front foot, just gets under this short delivery and goes over midwicket, off the mark finally
pulls square this time, doesn't get hold of it, gets two past square leg
stays back and defends a fullish delivery
wants a sharp single towards point, is sent back back by Ponting - and correctly because Alam is charging in swiftly
on target with both line and length, defended back to the bowler
length ball just outside off, Ponting lunges forward and pushes to mid-off
slightly back of a length, around off, Ponting hits on the up towards mid-off
keeps the length, slightly wide, and that allows Ponting to get a single to third man
White lunges forward, drops it towards cover and runs
front-foot pull, the odd ill-advised shot, it's just marginally back of a length, and Ponting misses it completely
Asif follows it up with a sharp in-ducker, Ponting gets the inside half of the bat for a single
starts off short and wide and is cut away to deep point
fuller, closer to off, defended towards cover
White won't be defending spin for long, sees a flighted delivery, clears the front leg, and goes through with the slog-sweep, is caught in the first row of the stand behind midwicket
late-cut,can't get it past point
he has literally worked it onto his stumps, a weird short really, starts off wide, turns away, and he is looking to flick it from way outside off, and plays it on to his middle stump
comes forward and defends a length delivery
cuts, gets a thick edge because it is too full for the cut
short of driving length, outside off, left alone
a legcutter, Voges throws a big cut at it, gets a soft edge, one bounce to Younis at slip
fuller, sharper, on the stumps, late into an attempt at a flick
short outside off, spin and bounce there, left alone
leading edge, looks to work it to on from outside off, the ball turns, takes a healthy edge and goes past slip
overpitched outside off, pushed down the ground to long-off
flighted around off, Ponting lunges forward and smothers it
another big move forward, pushed to cover
half-volley on the stumps, gives him an easy single down to long-on
back of a length outside off, gets it past point for a single
gets back and across, watches this short delivery onto his bat, and defends
full delivery, stays back to it, and defends towards mid-on
slightly slower delivery, defended towards cover and they run through because it is slightly to the left of the fielder
punched outside off, towards cover
puff of dust as this pitches on a length outside off, no puff of dust as it meets the middle of the Ponting bat, who plays it towards cover
quick delivery outside off, 99ks, left alone
strong off-side field, and he works this from middle stump towards fine leg
goes back and punches this short delivery through covers
angled into the pads, and turned around the corner
presses forward, opens the face towards point
lovely chip shot, no big back lift, just meets and goes inside-out over extra cover, didn't intend to clear the ground, just the ring, and he does
back of a length outside off, gets a thick edge with the slight leg cut, but there is no slip in place
short, pulled away easily, swivelling as he does so, keeping it along the ground, gets a single
looks to run this down to third man, but Rao is too close to him
same length, closer to the stumps, defended back to the bowler
short and wide, can't get it off the square, plays something in between the proper cut and the late-cut
fuller, Voges plays in front of his body, towards cover
short and wide, Ponting goes back and cuts, can't beat Alam at point
overpitched, half-volley, and gives him a single down the ground
short and wide and cut away, to the right of Alam at point, gets a risky single
into the pads, and worked away for an easy single
flighted outside off, Voges presses forward and defends
into the pads, and worked around the corner
short and wide, can't get enough into the cut shot, takes a single to the right of point
lovely shot, pulled from outside off, in total control of it, keeps it all along the ground and goes past midwicket for a couple
similar delivery, and he punches this one to sweeper-cover for a single
length ball outside off, defended towards cover
big shout for lbw, gets too far across himself, is hit in the front, but the little inside edge saves him. Well done Asoka de Silva
pushes forward and defends outside off
topisnner, Ponting defends with soft hands, but the ball threatens to roll along towards the stump
looks to cut but the googly cramps him up
another wrong'un, going down the leg side, misses out on the paddle shot
out-and-out offbreak, no disguise here, driven down the ground
lunges forward and defends outside off
flatter delivery, stays in the crease and pats it back to the bowler
floated around the middle line, defended towards midwicket
nicely played, dances down the track, opens up a bit, and lofts it over midwicket - first boundary since the 15th over
flatter delivery, keeps him on the back foot, defended
presses forward and smothers the spin
paddles this one from outside off, uppish but there is no short fine
topsinner, pushes him back, Ponting plays it with soft hands towards cover and takes a single
flat delivery outside off, played towards point
should for lbw as he plays the half-paddle-half-pull, but it's going over the stumps
driven on the up, one bounce to Younis Khan at cover
googly, flat too, keeps Ponting on the back foot
tossed up generously, Ponting gives it the textbook forward-defensive
the first bad ball of the over, fired down the leg side
another forward-defensive from Ponting
flat and full, gives away an easy single to long-on
shorter, Ponting goes back and pushes it down to long-on
short and pulled away towards deep midwicket
flighted around off, turning in, pushed to midwicket
nicely tossed up around off, flicked to midwicket
Ponting looks to work it to on from middle line, can't beat Younis Khan at straightish midwicket
flighted outside off, pushed to cover, Ponting wants one, Voges sends him back
little more flight, defended
quicker offbreak, 102ks, almost gets through the cut, Voges hasn't read it
another quicker delivery, 103ks, the legbreak, beats the cut, and misses the off stump by inches
tossed up this time, works it from off to the vacant on side, takes a single
pushes this wide of cover and takes a single
pushed down the ground, Malik gets a hand to it, but it's not enough to prevent the single
worked to the left of square leg and gets a single
leading edge, not for the first time for Ponting, but it bounces before reaching Malik
Ponting breaks the shackles and gets to fifty, this shot shows the pressure, steps out and plays the lofted shot with long-off in place, just gets it straight enough
swept away for single to follow the big four up
looks for the paddle sweep, turn and bounce, beats him, not called wide as it has spun from off and across down the leg side
flat delivery wide of off, punched away to sweeper-cover for a single
driven in front of his body, straight to cover
pushes this one past cover for a single
hangs this one in the air, 81ks, giving it time to spin, and it spins across Ponting who is squared up and is hit in the thigh
quicker delivery headed for off - as expected - Ponting goes back and defends
short, turns away, gives him room to get a single wide of cover
comes out of the crease, gets to the pitch of the ball, pushes it down to long-on
into the pads, worked away for a single

Ponting has holed out at long-on, flighted around middle, Ponting steps out, goes for it, doesn't get enough elevation, and Umar Akmal is cool a couple of feet inside the rope. Big wicket for Pakistan
flighted, gets too full, Hussey gets off with a single down to long-off
tossed up again, around off, defended to leg
this one is angled into the pads, and is worked away towards fine leg
a hint of reverse there, starts wide and tails in, Voges gets a single to wide of cover
a ripper to Hussey, starts leg, swings away, beats him just outside off
starts around off and angles it away, Hussey shoulders arms

another beauty, pitches leg, swings away, a noise as it passes Hussey, Sarfraz catches in front of the body, spontaneous shout, Reiffel calls not out - it has hit the back pad, what a ripper of a decision - it hadn't carried anyway
fuller, around off, and driven wide of sweeper-cover
bouncer, too high, called wide
back of a length, around off, defended towards cover
flighted around off, turns in, gets the inside half of the bat, takes a single wide of square leg
short, around off, cut away, not past point
shoulders arms to a flat delivery outside off
pushes forward and defends towards cover
goes deep into the crease and pushes it back to the bowler
right on the back foot, works this from outside off to vacant ring on the on side, gets a single
length ball around off, stays back and defends
bouncer, gets on top of it, keeps it down, the focus is in keeping it down rather than hitting it hard, and he places it well past midwicket, and hustles through for three
into the pads and helped away towards deep square leg
pitched up, driven down the ground, straight to mid-off
driven on the up, but can't pierce the tight off-side ring, no easy singles on offer either
back of a length, around off, Hussey goes deep into the crease and defends
that's a horrible delivery, fired in way down the leg side, Sarfraz gets a hand to it, but it would be too much to expect that to be collected. Arm ball gone wrong

a much better delivery, flighted, the overspin makes it dip, Voges has been suckered out of his crease, and the ball is not quite as full as it first seemed to be, and the result is a tame chip to midwicket. Game on
on target, around off, defended by James Hopes, the new batsman
into the pads, worked away to fine leg
short, slightly outside off, cut away to short third man
flat, into the pads, worked away around the corner
flighted around the leg line, turning towards off, Hussey comes forward and defends
short, slightly wide, cut towards backward point
punched off the back foot, can't get past cover
short and wide, cut away, but straight to backward point
topspinner, around middle, goes right back and defends
a touch too straight, and helped away to fine leg
short delivery, cut away to sweeper-cover
flat and full, outside off, Hussey lets it be
overpitched, driven down to long-off for a single
topspinner, around off, Hopes stays on the back foot and defends
swept from in front of the stumps, keeps it down, gets a single
slows this one down, 82ks, holds on to the surface, and Hussey is quick into the pull shot, the bottom edge evades the stumps
flighted around off, and driven down to long-on
tossed up on the off stump and driven back to the bowler
slower through the air, reaches out and cuts to sweeper cover
slower this time and Hussey defends to the off side
drops it towards mid-off and calls quickly for the run
straightens and clips his back pad as he gets forward to defend, optimistic appeal

good catch! Afridi pushes it a bit quicker through the air on the off stump, Hopes gets forward to defend but gets a thick outside edge, travels low to Younis at first slip who takes it inches off the ground
stays back and taps it to the off side for a single
flighted on the off stump and pushed wide of mid-off, sets off quickly, puts pressure on the fielder
pushes it wide of mid-off again and takes the single comfortably this time
gets forward and pushes him down to cover
gets forward and steers it to the off side
defended with soft hands to the off side
starts leg, swinging towards off, worked away to square leg for one
full delivery, hint of swing away from Johnson, defended towards cover
too straight, helped away to fine leg, gets a single
too straight again, flicked away square of fine leg, gets a couple
back of a length, gets a single to wide of cover
stays back of a length, no room for Johnson, gets a dot through
Malik is short, goes for a single to midwicket
too full on the pads, gets a single down to long-on
flighted around off, worked away into the vacant on-side ring for a single, Malik does well to chase and keep them down to one
tossed up outside off, Johnson shoulders arms
short and wide, and cut away for a single
topspinner, pushes him back into the crease,  Hussey can't find the gap square on the on side
Johnson plays straight to Alam at point, sends Hussey back, who has to dive in to beat the throw
Johnson pulls, is hurried into the shot, falls one bounce to deep square leg
helps this one down to third man, gets a single
offcutter, starts off, seams away, Johnson is beaten, Asif has a grin on his face
what a strike, what a time to hit it, pitched up with mid-off up, and he hits it clean over mid-off
worked off the hips, towards fine leg, gets a single
tossed up outside off, can't breach the cover ring but gets a single
nice topspinner, quick, on the stumps, no room, played back to the bowler
slightly slower, hit to the left of Malik, he hares across, fields, keeps this down to a dot
stays flat, across his body, enough room for Hussey to cut, and he finds the gap between the two points, cool as a cucumber
flighted around the pads, gets a single down the ground
fired on the pads, gets a single to fine leg, well bowled Malik, two big wickets in his 10 overs
slightly short of yorker, Johnson gets a single wide of mid-on
length ball, pushed across Hussey, he gets a thick edge towards third man

and what a time for Rana to strike, loose shot really, shortish, angled across him, Johnson cuts without getting close to it, the edge is snapped by Sarfraz, and Pakistan are in a huddle, they can feel it, they can sense a win around the corner
good delivery first up, back of a length, around off, defended off the back foot
nice inswinging yorker, that's the delivery that pays most of his bills, Hauritz can't do much with that
inswing, late inswing, length ball, tails in from outside off, pushed to midwicket
shape away from Hussey, hit towards cover, off the front foot, gets a single
short, outside off, bouncer, Hauritz lets it through to Sarfraz
Rao bowls short and wide, and Hauritz has cut it absolutely smack off the middle of the bat, wide of cover-point, what a shot for a No. 9 to be playing in this situation
slower ball, early into the shot, uppishly hit, but wide of Rao, mid-off keeps them in their creases
superbly bowled, yorker, around off and middle, played back to Rao
slower bouncer goes wrong, down the leg side
not much, just the one run, as Rao finishes off with a sharp delivery, on target, Hauritz defends it back to him
Hussey jumps out of the crease, pushes it down the ground, gets a single
back of a length, punched away crisply, takes off for a single, Afridi at extra cover has one stump to aim at, and misses with Hauritz not even in the frame
Hussey steps down again, doesn't get any room, Hussey drops and runs, Butt at short third misses again, Hauritz was a goner had he hit
superb delivery, back of a length, bounces extra, holds its line, beats him
smart shot, third man is square, and he deliberately opens the face on a length delivery, all along the ground it goes, and bisects the slip and the third man
slower ball, too straight, helped away to short fine for a single
fulltoss, yorker goes wrong, hit down to mid-off for a single
the rare poor delivery in the last 10 overs, short, leg side, fine leg up, Hussey accepts it with gratitude and pulls it past the lone fielder
full, on off, pushed down the ground to long-off, gets a single
Hauritz back away, Rao follows him with a short delivery, cramps him, Hauritz has to get the glove in the way to protect his ribs, priceless dot
inswinging yorker, digs it out, Hussey is always going for two as it limps towards long-on, and comes back easily, helped by a wide throw from Alam
slower short delivery, gets on top of it, runs it down to third man
Pakistan could have done without the overthrow, Alam - who has been fantastic in the field today - shies from backward point but Hauritz has made it, and there is nobody backing up either
full, gets a single to midwicket, helped by a fumble by Butt
swats this cross-batted, length ball, goes for the on side, hits one bounce to short midwicket
another swipe across the line, gets a single to wide of mid-on
lovely delivery, rises from back of a length, Hauritz rises with it, gets on top of it, and gets a single down to third man

he can't, he just drops it short. And he hates being called Mr Cricket, that's what he has been tonight, gets under the short delivery, pulls it between fine leg and deep square leg, and pumps his fist
oh is there another twist in here? Hauritz looks to work it to leg, moves too far across, the ball seams in, catches him on the crease, in front of middle, Rao you beauty
Harris can't do no wrong, don't shake his hand if you are in Perth, you might just turn to gold. He just saw a length ball, and swiped it over midwicket, gets two, scores level

it's a beamer, what drama, surely yorker gone wrong, lobs straight to mid-off, Afridi catches and appeals, but Asoka calls it a no-ball, just above waist, so fair call. Just wondering if the modern fashion of wearing trousers low would help getting such calls in your favour
